{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880537481,"sessionID":"ses_285471c81ffeH9NXpLJbwBQTNm","part":{"id":"prt_d7aba8565001o9ElV0S2bfk3lO","messageID":"msg_d7ab9ddf800104nnRVmy8jO3D2","sessionID":"ses_285471c81ffeH9NXpLJbwBQTNm","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-c039bd15c4c6431e9a3a6fc6a4378d5b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-028/proposal.md","content":"# AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## 概述\n\n| 属性 | 值 |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-028 |\n| Module | sdk-python |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (目的)\n\nProvide a Python SDK client (`AgentRuntimeClient`) for invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router. This client enables users to:\n\n1. Bootstrap session IDs via GET request to the Agent Runtime invocation endpoint\n2. Send JSON payloads to Agent Runtime workloads with session header `x-agentcube-session-id`\n3. Manage client lifecycle via context manager protocol\n4. Configure timeouts and connection pooling for HTTP requests\n\nThis is the second public client class exported from the `agentcube` package, complementing `CodeInterpreterClient` for code interpreter sessions.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Scope (范围)\n\n### 2.1 In Scope\n\n- `AgentRuntimeClient` class implementation with:\n  - Constructor accepting `agent_name`, `namespace`, `router_url`, `verbose`, `session_id`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`\n  - Context manager protocol (`__enter__`, `__exit__`)\n  - `invoke(payload, timeout)` method for sending JSON payloads\n  - `close()` method for closing HTTP session\n  - Session ID bootstrapping via GET request when `session_id` not provided\n\n- `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class implementation with:\n  - Constructor accepting `router_url`, `namespace`, `agent_name`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`, `pool_connections`, `pool_maxsize`\n  - `bootstrap_session_id()` method for GET request to invocation endpoint\n  - `invoke(session_id, payload, timeout)` method for POST request\n  - `close()` method for closing HTTP session\n  - Class constant `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n\n- Update `agentcube/__init__.py` to export `AgentRuntimeClient`\n- Update `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` to export `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n- Unit tests for both client classes\n\n### 2.2 Out of Scope\n\n- Control plane session management (handled by `ControlPlaneClient`)\n- Code interpreter operations (handled by `CodeInterpreterClient`)\n- Retry logic or circuit breaker patterns\n- Async API support\n- Authentication token handling on data plane (Router handles JWT)\n\n---\n\n## 3. Impact Analysis (影响分析)\n\n### 3.1 新增文件\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` public client class |\n| `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` internal HTTP client |\n| `sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime.py` | Unit tests for AgentRuntimeClient |\n\n### 3.2 修改文件\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `sdk-python/agentcube/__init__.py` | Add export of `AgentRuntimeClient` to `__all__` |\n| `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Add export of `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` |\n\n### 3.3 Upstream Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|\n| `requests` | HTTP client library (already in pyproject.toml) |\n| `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` for connection pooling |\n| `agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger` for logging |\n| `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception hierarchy (not actively raised by AgentRuntimeClient) |\n\n### 3.4 Downstream Consumers\n\n| Consumer | Usage |\n|----------|-------|\n| End users | Invoke Agent Runtime workloads via SDK |\n| Example scripts | `examples/agent_runtime_usage.py` (optional) |\n| Integration tests | `scripts/e2e_picod_test.py` (optional extension) |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Alternatives Considered (备选方案)\n\n### Alternative 1: Single unified client\n\nCombine `AgentRuntimeClient` and `CodeInterpreterClient` into a single `AgentCubeClient` with mode switching.\n\n**Rejected:** Different lifecycle semantics. CodeInterpreter requires control plane session creation/deletion; AgentRuntime only bootstraps session via data plane GET. Separate clients provide cleaner APIs.\n\n### Alternative 2: Async-first API\n\nImplement async/await based client using `aiohttp`.\n\n**Rejected:** SDK currently uses synchronous `requests` library. Adding async would double the API surface and require new dependency. Async support can be added in future AR if needed.\n\n### Alternative 3: Session ID passed directly to invoke\n\nRequire users to call `bootstrap_session_id()` manually and pass session_id to each `invoke()`.\n\n**Rejected:** UX would be poor. Client should manage session lifecycle transparently, similar to `CodeInterpreterClient` pattern.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Risks\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| Router URL required but not provided | Raise `ValueError` with clear message, same pattern as CodeInterpreterClient |\n| Session header missing in bootstrap response | Raise `ValueError` with message \"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\" |\n| Invoke called without valid session_id | Raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")` |\n| Connection pool exhaustion | Use configurable pool size defaults (pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10) |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Implementation Checklist\n\n- [ ] Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` in `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n- [ ] Implement `AgentRuntimeClient` in `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n- [ ] Update `agentcube/__init__.py` to export `AgentRuntimeClient`\n- [ ] Update `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` to export `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n- [ ] Write unit tests for `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n- [ ] Write unit tests for `AgentRuntimeClient`\n- [ ] Verify timeout tuple semantics: `(connect_timeout, timeout)`\n- [ ] Verify session header handling: `x-agentcube-session-id`\n\n---\n\n## 7. References\n\n- python-sdk/design.md — AgentCube Python SDK design\n- python-sdk/spec.md — SDK specification with AgentRuntime requirements\n- agentcube/code_interpreter.py — Reference implementation pattern\n- agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py — Reference data plane client"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/agentcube/__init__.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-028/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-028/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775880537464,"end":1775880537479}}}}
